More than 24,000 community members living near the Seven Forks Dams recently received water tanks donated by KenGen. This was in support of one of the measures to curb the spread of the coronavirus. The company donated 30 5,000â€“litre tanks to various shopping centres in 15 locations around Seven Forks Dams. In addition, each of the locations will receive 40 litres of soap, while critical areas such as dispensaries and police stations will benefit from 200 litres of sanitiser.